`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
Using Chebyshev distance (`Math.max(|chunkX|, |chunkZ|)`) for the Twilight Glade gate matches the chunk ring system's own square topology — a player 20 chunks away in any cardinal or diagonal direction sees the biome. Euclidean distance would create a circular exclusion zone that doesn't align with the square buffer rings.
